<p>OC2A started the day as a candidate and ended the day as a live production platform with three acknowledged open gaps and a much clearer picture of what those gaps are. The gateway is bound to 127.0.0.1. The database is running with auto-start and a recovery SOP. The Telegram alerting is silent, the Notion sync is green, and the business LinkedIn campaign is locked pending product approval. None of these statements were true at 00:45 AEST. All of them are true now.</p>

<hr class="divider">

<h2>What's Next</h2>

<ul class="next-list">
  <li>
    <span class="tag">Priority 1</span>
    Restore the Telegram bot token in the Keychain (service=<code>telegram-bot-token</code>, account=<code>ainchors</code>). Without it, every Telegram alert — DoD, cron dead-letter, daily burn — continues to fail silently. The auto-detect via heartbeat is now the only safety net.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class="tag">Priority 2</span>
    Apply for LinkedIn Marketing Developer Platform approval for the AInchors business account. Until that product is approved, the business LinkedIn campaign remains locked. Personal posting via Angie's account is live and operating normally.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class="tag">Priority 3</span>
    Confirm the historical OC1 <code>ainchors_nexus</code> data migration. Currently deferred pending Tailscale/RustDesk access to OC1. The fresh OC2A schema is operational; the historical data would close the audit gap.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class="tag">Security</span>
    Disable SIP on OC2A (Recovery-mode reboot + <code>csrutil disable</code> + <code>DisableLibraryValidation</code> plist) to unblock TKT-1000's iMessage channel build. Currently the only thing standing between Forge and the build is the physical intervention.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class="tag">Business</span>
    Begin Angie's personal LinkedIn post cycle with Aria. AW6-P1 missed the Tuesday slot — decide skip/push/override. AW6-P2 and AW6-P3 are ready for image generation and scheduling.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class="tag">Housekeeping</span>
    Update TOOLS.md to remove the stale "gog binary missing" note; <code>gog</code> is now configured for both Ken and Angie. Also clean up the <code>obs.db</code> empty-tables report from earlier in the day.
  </li>
</ul>

</div>
